# Mini Order System with FastAPI

## Project Overview
This project is a simple backend RESTful API for managing customer orders in a food delivery startup.  
It allows creating, reading, updating, and deleting orders as well as getting a summary of total orders and total value.  
The API is built using FastAPI and Python with in-memory storage (no database).

## Features Implemented
- Create new orders with customer name, item name, quantity, and price  
- Retrieve all orders  
- Fetch single order by ID  
- Update order status (pending, shipped, delivered, cancelled)  
- Delete an order  
- Get summary: total orders count and total value of all orders  
- Get all orders by a specific customer name  

## Setup Instructions

1. Clone the repository or download the code.  
2. Install the dependencies:
   ```bash
   pip install -r requirements.txt
